{"product_id": "368500", "page": 8, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-02", "text": "Pleasantly surprised by this title. I hated AC: Unity because it was so buggy and had really unsatisfying gameplay, it felt like Ubi had stripped down the mechanics of past titles without replacing them with anything.\nThis game is more close to the AC2 which is good because it focuses more on giving the player a fun experience than just having a bunch of monotonous activities that nobody wants to do. What I mean by this is that the devs knew that the strong suit of this game is the combat so you have much more missions that are action-oriented.\nThe story is still really stupid, it hasn't been good since the second installment so no surprise there sadly.\nThe game is still really fun though if you just don't pay close attention to the story.", "hours": 41.8, "username": "XIRB", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 8, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-01", "text": "So after 13 hours I will try to sum up the game with no spoilers:\nPros:\n-Great graphics\n-Interesting story\n-Great free roam\n-Actually hard combat that often forces you to go stealth\n-Many things to explore\n-Likeable characters\n-Plenty of freedom in transportation\n-Does include Karl Marx\nCons\n-Not a lot of weapon variety\n-Clunky controls while driving\n-Can't aim your weapons while in combat meaning you have to either quick fire or fight, making it rather difficult to fight more than one foe\nI give this game an 8.6/10", "hours": 30.0, "username": "Hender", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
