{"product_id": "368500", "page": 12, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Keyboard controls are a little finicky. Climbing is the most irritating. Conquering areas of the map quickly becomes tedious, but there are some areas that let you get creative with assassinations. Some of the main story missions feel repetitive, but\n. The side missions are the most repetitive, and I don't find myself doing them unless I'm short on funds. They mostly consist of transporting a person or object, following someone or protecting an important person; it seems Ubisoft loves to use filler in their games. The microtransactions that are available are for lazy folk who don't want to spend time gathering resources in game; you won't have any distinct advantage over people who keep their money.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "crebby", "products": 292, "early_access": false}
