{"product_id": "368500", "page": 18, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "London as a setting is really nice play to it, seems more open to move around and doesnt have those out of place ramps all over the place that make it obvious to you to climb on. The grappling hook is a bit OP IMO, can easily escape targets and climb buildings with with no effort, but i still dont mind having it in game. One of the main issues with the game is that climbing buildings and moving around in general isnt very smooth as you would sometimes climb the wrong ledge and then get spotted by the enemy, which is incredibly frustrating. Overall game has a decent story and main characters, has its flaws but would still recommend.", "hours": 34.6, "user_id": "76561198101416327", "username": "Fuego", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 18, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "When I bought this game (after playing all the previous AC games) my expectations where high. And at first the game did not live up to it. After abondoning it for about a year I started playing again an now I realy love the game. It is open, you are free to do and go anywhere. I has so many things to do it will keep you busy for a long time, been playing for 42 hours now and am only half way there. Fighting is still challanging, you have to keep an eye open in every corner to rebound incomming attacks. So in my opinion the price is realy worth it.", "hours": 57.2, "username": "Cyber Jocky", "products": 294, "early_access": false}
