{"product_id": "368500", "page": 19, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-18", "text": "Feels blank, frankly speaking. Repetitive tasks. Story does not really make you feel like you should care. Pretty shallow characters, hard to believe in their motivations. By the end of the game I was forcing myself to not uninstall before completing. And the final punch in the face: the Queen's missions after the main plot ends? Those should not be ever included in the game, they are too simple and too boring.\nNot to mention frequent crashes in random moments. But this is my experience, might be specific to my machine.\nOn the positive side, good graphics and a lot of historical (or made up) knowledge that you can find. But it feels like that's not nearly enough for the AC series title. I can only hope that AC Origins will be better.\nStill, thanks to the game developer's team for being able to create the game they have. I realize it might be hard to keep up the standards AC series has set in the past.\nCheers!", "hours": 69.4, "user_id": "76561198032831734", "username": "szklaniec", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
