{"product_id": "368500", "page": 20, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-14", "text": "It is a good game overall, got some new mechanics which are nice and the overall gameplay was better than in Unity. The side stories are nice and i liked the addition of carriages, it really improved traveling of semi long distances.\nBut the story is really bad for an AC game. The villains don't seem like Templars at all, just a bunch of disconnect figures who somehow screw with the lives of the citizens of London. It misses the AC story like the AC2 triology had, and the gameplay isn't new/awesome enough to compensate for it, like in Black Flag.\nOverall the game is good, well worth your money, just a new fun AC game to sink some hours in, but it won't be one i will remember for long.", "hours": 37.8, "username": "Aeilko", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 20, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-12", "text": "Unity may have been the more gruesome wound to the series, but Syndicate was the one that showed that the series had massively lost its way. Saying it's better than Unity isn't saying much, as true as it is, because Unity was a barely functional tech demo. Syndicate used the same tech, and proceeded to do nothing with it.\nHow to describe this game? Confused. Disjointed. Aimless. Hesitant. All of these words pretty much sum up the experience. It feels a lot like the Yakuza series or GTA4, in that we've reached the point where the game seems uncomfortable with the fact that the main characters are assassins. It also feels like they had no idea what to do with the setting, in that it spends most of its time shamelessly ripping off other game concepts. From the gang takeovers from Saint's Row, to the grappling hook from Batman, to the carriage stealing/racing from GTA, the fact is the game simply has no identity on it's own. It's as if the game is ashamed of the fact that it's about Assassins.\nThis game feels a lot like Revelations, in that it feels like the game has simply run out of ideas of what to do. It's also why the series took a year off after this, and it's clear why, because this game is the same way that London is in this game, a burnt out husk.\nIt's bland in every sense of the word, taking from every other successful series, and not really doing enough to be unique or interesting. It's a decent playthough, but you'll get more enjoyment out of other installments in the series.", "hours": 22.4, "user_id": "76561198008101873", "username": "Armads", "products": 504, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 20, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-11", "text": "Did you enjoy black flag? well you might enjoy this one! I don't know you . . . so . . can't make promises. But i can tell you that it is packed full of fun missions, has even cooler historical characters than black flag (i know, its hard to believe), and even cooler gadgets! plus its not unity (edit: it has come to my attention that some would consider unity 'a good game for the whole family' and in that case it is unity) so . . . play it, have fun and probs best to read the comments on the DLCs before buying them. Have fun!", "hours": 39.9, "username": "themagicwizardyfig", "products": 52, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
