{"product_id": "368500", "page": 20, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-09", "text": "It was my first assassin's creed that i bought and played myself and i was not disappointed. i just dont like the fact you dont have save slots but it didnt stop me from figuring out how to save them and play through the entire game twice. it helps that i absolutely loved the historical aspects of the entire game and how much i love the franchise before i even bought the game. evie and jacob have amazing chemistry and i enjoyed the perks and ways of playing both characters. evie also quickly became one of my favorite characters after ezio. i enjoyed the controls (which are so much better than AC:U. i hate the controls in that one so much and couldn't play through it at all lmao) and all in all, being the first game from AC that i bought and played, 100% satisfied. thank you for introducing me to this game. 100% gonna be buying all of the ones coming after it", "hours": 183.9, "user_id": "76561198204018768", "username": "mingh", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 21, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-07", "text": "Before Assasins Creed: Origins, I had this game on my personal list of top 2 or 3 best Assassins Creed games. It features a strong storyline with elements from AC: 2 and AC: Brotherhood as well as new features and gameplay mechanics that make this game one of the best in the AC series. The protagonists are refreshing and unique as well. Highly recommend.", "hours": 28.4, "username": "ODIN", "products": 31, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 21, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-06", "text": "Performance: decent enough and runs a lot smoother than Unity. 45-50fps average but it stays there, Unity I dropped into the 30s and 20s quite a bit. the performance boost between all-low settings and all-ultra except for antialiasing and gameworks is again nonexistent, so I ran most things closer to their highest.\nStory: Fairly weak, not as obnoxious as Unity's \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t excuse of a story.\nGameplay: I enjoyed it enough.\nThis is what Unity would have been if it hadn't been a colossal nightmare.", "hours": 48.6, "username": "LibertyDeathbat", "products": 92, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
