{"product_id": "368500", "page": 36, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-05", "text": "I know I only have a few hours, but it's enough to give it a brief review.\nAssassin's Creed Syndicate is a good recovery from the failure of a game-Assassin's Creed Unity. The mechanics felt on par with where the saga actually left off(AC4), with the combat feeling smooth and mostly complete. A few setbacks I noticed from AC4 were the throwing knives and quickshot with the pistol.\nAs for the optimization, it's pretty good but it could be better. Personally my FPS is all over the place, I go anywhere from 60 to 40 depending on where I am in the game. I've come to the conclusion that this game is very demanding in terms of VRAM rather than CPU intensive like other Ubisoft games.\nFrom what I have played so far, I like the game. The story is fun but the setting (19th century London) is my least favorite of the series, the game would be much better if the time period was different. I feel that the series can't really go past the 18th century without it becoming too modern for the AC series, technology advanced way too much in the 19th century for The Assassin's to stay on top of the pecking order.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "Maxfarace", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 36, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-04", "text": "From the perspective of a PC game this game was a sigh of relief. This is probably the most polished AC on PC and is very well optimized. The story is intriguing and innovative. This is surley something AC has never seen before and Ubisoft did a spendid job. If they keep making games like this the series will never die. Combat was polished and simplfied from AC Unity and handles much smoother. A character selection based on different playstyles was created praising the player for their style of play and not punishing them, Overall a great game. I wish I had picked this up sooner.", "hours": 2.4, "username": "\u261cGaz\u261e", "products": 172, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 36, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-04", "text": "After Replaying the whole series (and ones like these which I got burned out too fast to actually buy in the first place) in hype for Origins, I have to say, this is one of the better games in the latter half of the series. Gameplay wise it is fun, and not just stand and counter. Sure its nothing crazy technical, and the kill animations get pretty old, but overall much more engaging. Character wise, I really liked them a lot. I thought it brought something a little different than your usual broody or suave assassin stereotype. If you hated Unity (with good reason) this has some potential to give you a little more hope. (especially the fact that there is actually a modern day storyline, albeit not much. But still far more than previous entries, looking at you Unity.) If you already hate the series, dont buy it, its not going to change your mind.", "hours": 29.4, "username": "Yazz", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
