{"product_id": "368500", "page": 37, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-29", "text": "Recovering from the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665how that was Assassin's Creed Unity was surprising. I still however, feel a large disconnection from the story. Being called \"initiate\" barely allows you to create a relationship with the character outside of the animus as opposed to the Desmond era (the past few games I felt like this). However the story inside the animus is fluid, exciting and feels good.\nBeautiful world, fluid combat.\nCon - I hate the grappling hook. Feel like it destroys a key element of Assassin's Creed.\nNonetheless I enjoyed this game.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Cyanide", "products": 214, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
