{"product_id": "368500", "page": 60, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-05", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed game so far in my opinion. The graphics in the game are absolutely gorgeous. Especially the lightning is very impressive. The Victorian London is highly detailed and feels authentic. If you ever visited London it\u2019s easy to recognize the places. The engine ran very well on my AMD machine (R290 4GB, FX-9590, 16GB RAM, W10). No stuttering, no short freezes. Just prefect. The story missions didn\u2019t feel repetitive at all and having two player characters made them really interesting.", "hours": 40.6, "user_id": "76561198015983358", "username": "megaD", "products": 170, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
