{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-11", "text": "This is one of the best Assassins Creed games to date! Finally they have main character(s)that you like and can feel for in a AC game. Jacob is Jacob but Evie is one of the best and most intressting characters that i have played in a AC game in a long time. AC2 + Unity = Syndicate.", "hours": 89.2, "username": "kabbzter", "products": 325, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-10", "text": "If AC 2 and 4 did not exist this would be my favorite Assassin's Creed game, they've learned enough from Unity's goods and bads to make a decent balance in this one.\nThe only downside that bothered me is the fact that the gaps between buildings are far too wide now so you'll NEED to rely heavily on your rope launcher.", "hours": 49.7, "user_id": "76561198210834153", "username": "Red Rohan", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-10", "text": "Pros and cons style:\nBeautiful graphics.\nFantastic (10/10) atmosphere.\nFantastic (10/10) audio.\nGreat character design.\nFantastic animations.\nInteresting premise.\nAMAZINGLY HORRIBLE controls. (LIterally the worst control scheme and camera I've ever saw anywhere on anything or could possibly imagine. This is the quarter claw game of video games, or the \"Linux FOSS developer with a hardon for CLI decides to design a GUI and parkour control scheme for a video game\" game.)\nEngine is pretty resource heavy though it looks good enough to justify it.\nStory is rather disjointed and all over the place.\nUPlay is essentially cancer to appease mouthbreathing accountants who think DRM makes them money.\nCombat is basically frozen moose spunk in a bucket, on rollerskates. With knives.\nInane DLC with very 'nickle and dime' shenanigans for in-game currency and such nonsense. (Hi, Cheat Engine.)\nTends to crash for no real reason other than Uplay/DRM garbageaids.\nIt's like a company with amazing funding decided to make a AAA game, and succeeded, then listened to their 'money guys' for suggestions for additional changes, but didn't have enough money left to hire someone other than the minimum-wage, Gentoo-running neckbeard janitor to come up with a control scheme or GUI.\nRegardless, it's...positive aspects outweigh it's negatives. It's pretty damn close, though, the controls are THAT bad.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Butterball", "products": 231, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-09", "text": "This game is a 10 for me, put the past week straight into this and just can't put it down. The atmosphere, the writing, the lead characters, even the people you do missions for all have some significance and their own charm. Even the more threatening Templar characters have likable qualities.The gameplay is spot on, best of any AC title to date. The combat is lightning fast, brutal (double, triple and quadra kill animations are all INSANE). Moving around feels right finally, up and down free run, the grappling hook is more a thank you to AC fans, instant gap cover and instant tower climbing (getting Eagle points is a piece of cake). Best of all, it's all optional. Stealth killing is better suited to Evie while heavy combat is Jacob's forte.\nPros\n- Victorian London setting\n- The Fry Twins (unbelievable dialog and chemistry, simply masterful)\n- Strong supporting cast and villains\n- Graphics\n- building up the rooks\n- Beautiful art direction\nCons\n-Tiring companion rep grind\n- Broken up story\n- side activities grow old\n- overly simplistic combat", "hours": 16.3, "user_id": "76561198011965365", "username": "Saint Aaron", "products": 1706, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-02-08", "text": "For me the game wasn't all that I thought it was going to be. I had played it on another system and it was not that great. The game itself was all buggy, I couldn't understand or follow the storyline very well. Maybe that's my fault i am not completely sure lol. However I would like my money back from this purchase.", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561198102745021", "username": "Johnny B", "products": 31, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-07", "text": "A definite improvement over Unity, but the game still has its fair share of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665br>PROS:\n- Great setting\n- Interesting characters\n- Good story\n- It's not like Unity at all\nCONS:\n- Modern day stuff sucks.\n- The combat \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing garbage and only works when it wants to\n- Climbing is awkward because the controls only work half the time\n- Story was somewhat predictable\n- Too many collectibles\n- Helix credits. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you Ubisoft  for dragging that\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665into here aswell.\n- Uplay\n- No hidden blade combat\nAll in all, it's a pretty good game, but it has a long way to go. 6/10", "hours": 72.1, "username": "\u00d8rjan", "products": 176, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-07", "text": "Probably the best Assassins Creed game i've played.\nSyndicate is a mix of refined gameplay with an interesting premise.\nBoth Evie and Jacob are likeable compared to previous assassins, cough Ezio, cough Connor.\nThe gameplay whilst a similar premise to previous games introdces new mechanics and enemy types for to face.\nThe world itself is gorgeous and represents London incredibly, however the borough takeovers get boring eventually.\nThe regular side missions for historical figures are a lot of fun!\nOnly downsides was the final boss being incredibly easy and boring, furthmore I encountered a couple of bugs with carriages but other than this, the game was incredible.\nI'm yet to touch the DLC but I cannot wait.", "hours": 41.9, "username": "Carned", "products": 1082, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 72, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-07", "text": "Brutally awesome! Currently 35 hours of game play and 62% complete of the game! Yes I do the side stuff on searching for items, but still great bang for the buck. (Bought it on sale +-25 EUR). Even tho it has partial Steam controller support, you wont have an issue with it. But you must start the game from steam, and the controller pre-connected. It wont connect when game is launched.. (That the only downside) Story wise, I found it awesome. I won't spoil anything, if you want to know some more about the story I would suggest you Google that!\nPs. If there are missions you cant get throu, there are a lot of forums ans wiki's for the hole friencise of Assassins Creed.", "hours": 45.5, "username": "JA-Francis", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
