{"product_id": "368500", "page": 82, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-31", "text": "Industrial age London setting is absolutely amazing and beautiful just to roam around.  It's good game except it's way too easy.  There are no large patrols of enemies, you will have your gang to help you, you have a semi-auto pistol, and it's too easy to run away.\nThe game itself is pretty well optimized and actually runs smoother and requires less hardware to run at 60fps than AC Unity.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "Zbig", "products": 346, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 82, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-31", "text": "To start it off let me put it this way - I have played every single AC ever released, including some versions people didn't even know existed such as the one for the original PSP.\nSyndicate quite possibly has characters lovable enough to be compared to Ezio, even if not quite there. The story as far as I have got into the game seems fairly intriguing. The climbing actually works, especially when compared to the disaster that was unity.\nAll in all if we only consider the game through gameplay, characters and story it is up there in the list, unfortunatelly all that experience is being heavily impacted by the rather lack-luster optimisation of the game.\nTo put it in perspective in order to actually be able to play the game decently with my oc'd gtx 970 and i5-3570 (Not the best, but more than enough for ultra on say witcher 3) I need to run the game in windowed mode (It freezes like no tomorrow and stutters otherwise) in addition to having to modify the priority from my task manager. Additionally I need to limit the game to 60 fps via third party software if I ever want to consider using a carriage otherwise it will freeze every five to six seconds.\nIf you can implement these things yourself the game will run fairly well, however to many this might be a deal breaker. Do consider this before buying the game for yourself.", "hours": 13.7, "user_id": "76561198034538306", "username": "Leopold", "products": 511, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 82, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-30", "text": "Mediocre story, good mechanics and setting, Looks great.  Wondeful characterization especially for Evie and some of the supporting characters. Jacob is a bit of a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 but you don't really have to play as him. It would be great if you could just play as Evie. Ubisoft should have the balls to have a solo female protagonist in an Assassin's Creed game. Its the most fun since Black Flag. I enjoy the stealth action of games like this and the Arkham games which it borrows from. I'd reccomend with the caveats I mentioned", "hours": 50.3, "user_id": "76561198132286694", "username": "alawder1210", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
