{"product_id": "368500", "page": 85, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-27", "text": "Good:\nThe city is gorgeous and it feels more real and alive than Paris did in Unity. The main characters are well written and voiced, especially Evie. Unity felt like a tech demo, Syndicate does not. All in all, it's a good AC game, just don't expect it to be totally different from what you've seen in the previous games.\nBad:\nAs I said, the city is gorgeous. But copy pasted buildings it feels like. I experienced the first 2 hours as great. But now I felt like I wanted my 20 euro's back. It's a great game. I experienced something wonderful the first 2 hours. But I just, feel like there's better titles for under 20 euro's. Sorry ACS..", "hours": 2.2, "username": "GibrAh a.k.a", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
