{"product_id": "368500", "page": 88, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-17", "text": "Hello everyone. Well, i played more than 3 hours so my expierience isn't good with this game, but after this 3h i can say the optimalization s*cks. (GTX 970 MSI 4GB & i5 6600k=30-35 ULTRA)  Addictions and fails: down below: (I'm reviewing this game on the highest grapihcs settings)\nGood stuff:\n-Architecture\n-Harismatic characters\n-Intresting story\n-Gameplay mechanics (nice stealth mode, finally)\nFails:\n-Optimalization (It's a joke)\n-LOD (details desapears in 30m, even on the highest settings, so it looks pretty sh*tty)\n-Textures (Characters the most)\n-Enemies inteligence\nBasicly, i recomend this game coz of the amazing architecture, climat and pretty solid gameplay mechanics.\nPeace out lads.     (PC SPECS ON MY STEAM PROFILE)", "hours": 29.6, "user_id": "76561198196725950", "username": "Lord Jim", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 88, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-14", "text": "The game is extermely buggy on the pc. At important moments in the game, the game just crashes and stops working. I bought a compact disc + tried installing form steam - both lead to the same thing. I have a windows 10 64 bit OS. All the rest of the games e.g. Battlefield, Witcher3 work perfectly find on my alienware pc.\nThis leads me to believe that this game's code is buggy.\nAlso the interface for gaming on PC is really uncomfortable. Ubisoft created this game for the console and without any changes slapped it on the PC environment  - a really shoddy job.\nEven during gameplay I found a bunch of bugs (just like unity). My character started to fly around after crashing into a enemy horse cart.\nThe interface to jump around building is okay, but it so hard to get down to the ground (a weird key combo gets you back to the ground) which is really irritating when you are working with full blown enemy attacks.", "hours": 48.6, "user_id": "76561198347678222", "username": "KilledYou", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
