{"product_id": "368500", "page": 89, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-12", "text": "This game has too many missing necesseties. Everything from a structured story to balanced combat. The Story in peticular is extremely unstructured and lacks purpose, which is a buzzkill coming from a highly narrative game. The game is waaay too simplistic and not nearly detailed in the right areas. It seems there is only three different NPCs, even in gang lords, it's ridiculous.\nNow, the game strives on stunning visuals and the in-game environment, which it does strive on. Although, it seems like they focused way too much on visuals rather than what really matters, gameplay.", "hours": 36.5, "user_id": "76561198205852031", "username": "hansenite", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 89, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-12", "text": "Im a big fan of the series and the overall storyline but anyone can pickup this game and get in it because these is little to no focus on any of the backstory at this point aside from the odd disembodyied comment witch you can care less about.\nNow the actual game itsself is great, the missions, story and historical figures are diverse and captivateing and theres much much more the game has to offer so i definetly recommend this to any fan of the seris or anyone looking to get into the series.\nAs far as gamplay is concerned, i rank it as the best one in the series to date.", "hours": 166.8, "user_id": "76561198131031609", "username": "VikFreeze", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
