{"product_id": "368500", "page": 92, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-04", "text": "It's not the best Assassin's Creed game out there, but it is enjoyable. The story is interesting, despite the lack of character development and I never really feel like I get a connection with either of the main characters in the game. Otherwise it is good game.\nThe reason why I can't recommend the game though, is the constant crashing (ACS.exe has stopped working) which UBISOFT has failed to fix. You'll find multiple threads on different forums about the error, but none of the proposed solutions actually works. The error (in my case) occurs when you've finished a mission or a story arch, which happens often.\nBuy the Ezio collection (just released in late 2016) if you want to really experience Assassin's Creed at its best.", "hours": 50.5, "user_id": "76561198011944356", "username": "Verzada", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
