{"product_id": "368500", "page": 97, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-26", "text": "You can play it with a PC in the minimum with everything at low and at 720p, which isn't that bad for me, AND get a stable 60 FPS (which is not common). =)\nAfter a while it becomes repetitive but all AC games are pretty much repetitive. The atmosphere of recreating a vintage London is perfect, specially if you ever read a novel by Charles Dickens, F.H. Burnett, A.C. Doyle, etc... you'll kinda \"feel at home\" playing this game. =)\n(Also worth mentioning that the child character can be a \"Sara Crewe\" on her own) =)\nTotally recommended *IF* you like AC games and it's on sale. =)\n[Update]:\nMy system:\nFX 8320, 8 gb RAM, Windows 7 64 bits.\nR9 270 2gb", "hours": 48.3, "username": "Abelardo", "products": 214, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
