{"product_id": "368500", "page": 104, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-22", "text": "This is by far my second favourite Assassin's Creed, after Assassin's Creed II. Ubisoft came back to reality and to the roots of their most famous last generation videogame saga with this title, REMOVING MULTIPLAYER / CO-OP, giving us a thrilling plot set in the Victorian London near the end of 1800, two charismatic characters that are twins and both of them gave me the same feeling I felt when I was playing as Ezio Auditore the first time.\nI recommend this game to every fan who still believes there's hope for the Assassin's Creed saga, cause the first stepping stone for Ubisoft for their redemption is this game, Assassin's Creed Syndicate.", "hours": 38.4, "username": "Zero", "products": 374, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 104, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-21", "text": "Suprisingly good game, especially after the failure that was Unity. The controls are, thankfully, responsive and the gameplay is smooth. There's some issues, like unskippable opening credits, microtransactions in the single player mode, and it crashes a lot after mission completion for me, but everything else is done well and the story is fun. I'm not sure if Agnes could possibly become as obese as she is in that time of London, and I seriously doubt there were as any women with any reasonable power back then as there are in this game, but I guess Ubisoft must cater.", "hours": 14.6, "username": "MarioDragon", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
