{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-16", "text": "One of the best Assassin's Creed game ever !\nBuy the game ! What are you waiting for ?\n-Awsome graphics !\n-Incredible story !\n-Nice side quest !\n-Good fight !\n- Awsome ending !\n-Ladies and gentleman we are Jacob and Evie Frye ! And as from this moment, you all work, for us !!!\n-And.....nice DLC ''Jack the Reaper'' !\n10/10 !!!", "hours": 100.0, "user_id": "76561198202177471", "username": "LuciferCreed", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-16", "text": "Open world games have become a joke. Just repetitive things to do, unlocking skills and weapons that are only there to dilate the time you spend in the game, collecting meningless\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.. Just give me a good history and if it's going to be short I'll not care. Just don't charge +60 eur as it's becoming a norm today.\nOn the other hand, I love the Victorian era and the design of the city and all the people roaming, selling things etc, it's very well done. Ambient is great and you can spend a few hours just wandering and admiring their work.", "hours": 63.5, "user_id": "76561198001091097", "username": "archaon_archi", "products": 198, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-14", "text": "This game is not what you want it to be. If you're looking into it because it looks like something new and fresh its not. To start off I want to say that I have a maxed out pc and the game looks worse than the screenshots ive seen. Plus its not too optimized which is confusing because a lot of people are saying that its \"okay enough\" which in fact this is not the case. The first five SECONDS of my game I experienced a bug and i felt like I had to be careful because the game seems so fragile and it takes away from everything good that this game has at the very least. On the other hand its all around boring. Repetitive missions and side quests, and the game makes me not feel for the characters. If you are starting to get into AC, I reccommend getting black flag. Save your money.", "hours": 35.2, "user_id": "76561198119688150", "username": "TheLast_Lion", "products": 57, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-14", "text": "\"Syndicate\" - a curious story, forcing the opposition to take another look at the Assassins and the Templars. It's damn snazzy London, but so that it is sure to want to visit in person - later on, when prices will fall (yes, we are optimists). But this seems to be positive points end.\nEvery year we get from the fresh parts of the series a new beautiful city and a couple of innovations, not always successful. Nevertheless, Assassin's Creed is loved by many, and therefore, it is enough. Just not buggy and hook-cat to the goal always got.", "hours": 129.7, "username": "fQoulke", "products": 292, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-13", "text": "Expected a beautiful open world with great optimization, fun gameplay, and good stealth mechanics in Mafia 3. That game failed me, refunded that and got all of that and more with this masterpiece. One of the best looking games I've ever seen. London is awe inspiring.", "hours": 29.4, "username": "Furi0sa", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-12", "text": "Very beautiful graphics. Sincerely enjoyed walking arounf Victorian London.\nSuper awesome mechanics ( lot's of different combinations)\nGood amount of side missions\n\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 story.\n[There's one susprise mission which I liked]\nThere really isn't any story whatsoever.\nYou get to play both Evie and Jacob which I really enjoyed.\nI didn't like the fact that they give you a little taste of Jack the Ripper, to encourage you to buy the DLC later. lol", "hours": 130.8, "username": "CheshireKat", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 106, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-11", "text": "SPOILERS ARE HIDDEN!\n+ Great setting, London really feels alive and looks realistic\n+ Two main characters, and both of them have their own skillset (Evie's skills are stealth based, while Jacob specializes in combat). Both characters are also interesting and dialogue between them is great!\n+ Story left me wanting for more, and in a good way! Hopefully this is not the last time we'll hear of Jacob and Evie Frye.\n+ Plenty of things to do and historical people to meet. I've so far played through the main story, but I still have many side quests and liberation missions to do.\n+\n+ Talking about the liberation missions, they are not the same thing all over again. They differ from capturing a criminal to setting child workers free and killing the factory's headman\n+ Fighting animations and assassinations look briliant\n+ Whenever you need to eliminate your next main target, you'll get a chance to perform an unique kill on them. Don't waste these chances, they are awesome.\n- While Ubisoft has otherways done surprisingly good job with optimization, game stutters a lot when you're driving a carriage. In my case, it freezes for about 1-3 seconds every now and then and works fine other than that. Not game breaking though, since the main idea of the game is not cruising around with a carriage. (I have i7 + GeForce 970 + 8gm ram so I do not know how this problem is present on different rigs)\n- At times, free running feels clumsy. Often times I found myself climbing a wall I didn't want to climb etc. Unity had done better job in free running tbh.\nI have played every Assassin's Creed game, except for Revelations and Rogue, and this one might even be my new favorite. I highly recommend this brilliant product.", "hours": 45.9, "user_id": "76561198021134581", "username": "urbanwalrus", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-11", "text": "This is what Unity should have been all along. Lovely posh english accents mixed with an efficient, flowing city. I love Assassin's creed and I've wasted tons of hours hunting templars. Would hunt again, even without the accent.", "hours": 74.6, "username": "Increddibelly", "products": 198, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-10", "text": "Basically the same as all the other open world sand box games. World didn't feel like it was breathing for me. Cash shop options in like every menu was a major turn off.", "hours": 42.6, "username": "GRIZLEDORF", "products": 82, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
