{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-08", "text": "Really enjoyed it. The plot is a bit meh but the gameplay is classic AC gameplay. Every now and then had some stuttering bugs (3 or 4 times during the playthrough) but rebooting the computer and it was back to normal.\nBuying helix credits doesn't work properly though it took a couple days for them to be added to my account and when they were it wouldn't let me spend them, so stay away from those.\nJack the Ripper DLC is pretty good.\nBasically, it's pretty, fun, has the odd bug, and you should ignore the e shop.", "hours": 49.7, "username": "pjplatypus", "products": 763, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-08", "text": "love it!", "hours": 39.7, "user_id": "76561198304225388", "username": "109", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-07", "text": "Although it has it's bugs like any Assassin's Creed game, Syndicate is a well written tale of liberation with a perfect ending.\nWith sub-Unity graphics (still good, and less lag), the game still looks stunning on high PC settings and is fairly well optimized. Each of the 10 main villians (8 + Thorne and Starrick) were very well written for the compartively brief time they played their roles. Likewise, the main protagonists, the Frye twins, share a dynamic that truely encapsulates their sibling rivalry and different approaches to missions. (This is the part where I review the present day animus part of the story but honestly who really cares, still cool though). The grappling hook mechanic with the twins' rope launchers also makes stealth and traveling much more convienient. Meanwhile, traversing the metropolis of Victorian London on foot, while sometimes clunky, can mostly remain fluid and works well with the combat (most of the time). It's truely a shame that Unity's utter failure had a negative impact on this game's sales but it's a masterpiece in my eyes", "hours": 34.7, "username": "Qylo", "products": 132, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-07", "text": "no..", "hours": 2.3, "username": "Vulture", "products": 354, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-06", "text": "The game engine is absolutely awful.. Buggy cloth physics and movement and delayed input. I have not finished the campaign yet as the input lag made the game unplayable for me.", "hours": 44.6, "username": "boswelja", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-06", "text": "If you want lazy freerunning or none at all most of the time buy this. If you want half\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665combat thats somehow worse than unity play this. If youre looking for a game that will make call of duty seem original in terms of story play this. If you want something good play black flag, or rogue, or any of the ezio trilogy; just not this.", "hours": 15.8, "user_id": "76561198121085164", "username": "TerrificCake", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 107, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-06", "text": "So much to do, so much to see.\nThe missions are varied from annoying to sublime, the characters do seem to play similarly, but that could be user bias.  The grapple hook is a great introduction but not as insane as Just Cause's version which is understandable.\nThis is a game to take your time over and level up before taking on the take over missions.  It's a shame you're not sending out teams of assassins around the world on missions as that was an interesting diversion and a way to acrue money and materials.\nI recommend this game, and am also glad they're taking a break from an annual release.  Hopefully the next chapter in the installment will be able to introduce new elements along with the familiar.  Perhaps some (limited) gun-fu?", "hours": 32.5, "username": "sidrat", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
