{"product_id": "368500", "page": 108, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Syndicate is, so far, the best game in the series. It definitely trumps the likes of Assassins Creed 2 and Black Flag. The London environment feels so lifelike and the combat is extremely satisfying.  I found the story to be primarily engaging, running around London helping out the likes of Alexander Graham Bell, Charles Darwin and even Queen Victoria, but at some sections it felt a bit lackluster. Syndicate adopts Unity's revamped parkour system, making movement seamless and fun. If only it had used some other assets from Unity, I would have liked to see more customization when it came to costumes - they all kinda felt the same to me.\nAssassins Creed: Syndicate is a fantastic game and is definitely worth your time.\n9/10", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Make-A-Wish Kid", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
