{"product_id": "368500", "page": 110, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-17", "text": "Assassin's Creed Syndicate is a very fun game, but a terrible port. About 97% of ubisoft ports are garbage. But the only bad port stuff about this one is that when you are on a train, or driving a carriage, the game stutters like hell, and when you get off, the textures look like playdough, and take about 5 seconds to go back to normal. But besides the stuttering on trains and carriages, the game is very fun, and I am enjoying the game alot. Bought it for $40, and bought a few DLC's, so for the price of ~$60, I am pleased with the amount of content in it.\nFinal Verdict- If you don't mind stuttering when on carriages and trains, then buy the game, it pretty fun. []7.5/10[]", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Eddie Murphy", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
