{"product_id": "368500", "page": 110, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-13", "text": "When I first played this game, I was still incredibly\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665that they'd killed off Desmond.  I'll be honest, I loved the 1st Assassin's Creed, and it felt like Ubisoft was descending further and further into insanity with every additional game they released in the franchise.\nSo I decided in five minutes that Syndicate was just as bad and I moved on.\nWell... many hours of Black Flag and Rogue later, I came back to Syndicate to see if I'd missed anything and......\nJust woah.  I missed EVERYTHING.\nThis game is incredibly fun (especially if you're willing to take some time and read all the animus/database entries as it adds the context and depth I felt were missing in Unity and all the other post-desmond games).\nGet Syndicate and take your time with it, it's difficult not to love.", "hours": 97.3, "user_id": "76561197997954781", "username": "Garrett", "products": 255, "early_access": false}
