alright. 7.5/10, I'd grab it if you like Assassin's Creed and you don't care that its the same as the last. If you're new to the series, I'd recommend picking up AC4 or AC Rogue, both are good and they have badass ship combat. This is a decent pick I'd say, though, and if the time period interests you, I say go for it.", "hours": 22.7, "username": "dogboat333", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 111, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-09-12", "text": "Really going to be my last AC. I always disliked the anti-Christian rhetoric pervasive throughout the series, but heard good things about the gameplay. The gameplay is still stuck about a decade back with the excruciatingly slow and unresponsive combat animations (seriously, SoM figured it out, how can Ubisoft not take a page from their book). The story is still trash and what's worse the stability is absolutely atrocious. In about 9 hours I have had no less than 10 crashes. This is really unacceptable.", "hours": 30.2, "user_id": "76561197983131478", "username": "loki1944", "products": 421, "early_access": false}
