{"product_id": "368500", "page": 113, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-27", "text": "+Jacob and Evie got a little of personality, and they aren't \"paper assassin's\"\n+beautiful graphics and STUNNING living city\n+no annoying lags\n+historical charters like Bell, Dickens, Darwin, Marks, Disraeli\n+louds of great side activities like hood liberation, cargo hijack etc\n+amazing side quests where we become sort of employee  of historical charters\n+brilliant soundtrack\n-storry is quiet short and it maybe doesn't use all the potential of XIXth century London", "hours": 151.7, "username": "bore", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
