{"product_id": "368500", "page": 114, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-17", "text": "Awesome Game! I rarely do reviews but after seeing some of the bad ones I feel like I should give this game a little justice. The last game in the series that I played was Black Flag and I loved it. I wasn't much of a fan of the eras following it so I took a break for a while. Six hours into Syndicate and so far the story is awesome and the gameplay is fantastic. It runs very smooth on medium level graphics on my laptop with a Geforce GTX 965M and still looks great. After a little practice and upgrades the fights feel better than any Assassins Creed I've ever played. I've found myself intentionally walking slow into dangerous areas to emphasize the level of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665kicking that was about occur.\nThe one downside that I've found so far is the carriages tend to be hard to navigate and a bit clunky. Otherwise I highly recommend this game!", "hours": 34.2, "user_id": "76561198046420939", "username": "jrd.myers", "products": 47, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 114, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-17", "text": "I really enjoyed this part in the series unlike Unity, this game's plot makes you actually want to continue, and continues on the main story in the \"real world\". I had some problems getting it to stop crashing, which was easily fixed by running both the game and uplay as admin, and changing the Setdriverworkaround to 1 in the AC.ini in documents. I then had alot of lag which was odd as I've seen others run it fine with lesser systems, but that was also fixed by going into my Nvidia control panel and changing Vsync to adaptive and Max frames rendered to 1. The game was like butter after those fixes. Hopes this helps people.", "hours": 26.4, "user_id": "76561198032119718", "username": "Grubbs008", "products": 230, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
