{"product_id": "368500", "page": 115, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "Assassin's Creed Syndicate is a great game... at least it would be if I could play it. A recent patch has broken the game leaving thousands of players with a product that won't launch.\nThe issue is related to a warning that used to pop up about old video drivers. Before the patch you could click OK and the game would start, but now the pop up no longer appears so the game just sits there with the AC logo forever displayed. This issue persists even after downloading the latest Nvidia drivers.\nAny one considering buying this game be warned! YOU could shell out the cash for this game only to be left with a product that doesn't work.\nTo my knowledge Ubisoft has been very silent about the issue as no one I've found has gotten a reply about it, so until Ubisoft gets off their asses and lets me play the game I paid for consider me disgruntled. And to think I trusted them again after Unity...", "hours": 13.5, "username": "Onionfey", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 115, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-12", "text": "After an emotional installment in the series this game was light hearted and fun to play. The conquering of Burroughs is a good challenge to keep between the story. The levelling up of skills and the skill tree is a great addition to the game. The switching of character gave a fresh feel to the dynamics. Overall it was an immersive game though it lacks an emotional appeal. The game crashes very frequently Everytime a Burrough leader is defeated. Other than that the game Mechanics are wonderful.", "hours": 42.9, "username": "Whit3Rook", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
