{"product_id": "368500", "page": 123, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "I'll keep it short and simple.\nMy favorite game so far is AC2. AC Syndicate is the first AC game after the Ezio trilogy that felt like an AC game again.\nFree running and harpooning/ziplining through London feels great. The whole game feels great actually. Like the assassins got a bit more modern.\nI really like seeing a female main character in AC since most AC games are male dominant.\nBut I love both main characters. But also how they implemented this in the game.\nWith the skill trees there are skills available only to Evie or Jacob, making Evie a more stealthie character and Jacob a more combat character.\nOfcourse this game has some cons as well, the region takeover is repetitive. But every game has its flaws. Generally I feel that Assassins Creed Syndicate is a step in the right direction.", "hours": 42.4, "user_id": "76561198028448671", "username": "Whojoo_", "products": 107, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 123, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "It's a fun game. Not very deep but plenty of fun if you like using stealth to accomplish goals. The recreation of Victorian London is outstanding. I've a few quibbles one of which is the seeming inability to change the difficulty level. However it seems to scale to your proximity to your target i.e. the foes get more challenging as you get closer to the goal. I also dislike not being able to manually save my progress.\nRunning it on a gtx  970. Had one crash so far but other than that the game runs pretty smoothly and looks great. I haven't tested the fps and not sure I feel the need to given how smooth it is so far. If you're running it on an integrated graphics chip or something less than a 700 series card just forget it. If you're going to try on a laptop that's not a recent gaming laptop don't waste your money. Also update your Nvidia driver and make sure you update your Uplay account i.e. uninstall it and reinstall it and that way the game will run. Have fun!", "hours": 17.6, "user_id": "76561198021821154", "username": "tombeatster", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
