{"product_id": "368500", "page": 163, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-06", "text": "Pretty much the best Assassin's Creed game, up there with the Ezio trilogy and Black Flag.\nThe grappling hook is a great new way to move around the huge city of London, a pretty decent story, no present day sequences, plenty of different styles of side missions, mix up the play style of being a brawler or a stealth based character.", "hours": 91.3, "username": "Fart of Presto", "products": 4802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 163, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-06", "text": "This version is one of the best Assassin\u2019s creed I played so far, together with Black Flag.\nThe rope launcher is cool and the fact that you have 2 characters. The graphics are quite amazing, much better than in previous versions. You do get bored quickly after playing the game for 30 hours.\nIt\u2019s an easy game but sometimes it\u2019s repetitive. A few times the game crashed and I was on my windows desktop with the error message saying \u201cAC.exe has stopped working\u201d\nI would give this game 8/10\nI would only recommend this game when you're fan of the Assassin's Creed genre or when you like to play open world action adventure games.", "hours": 30.9, "username": "Cedde", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
