{"product_id": "368500", "page": 163, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-04", "text": "The good: decent PC performance (unlike Unity), great visuals and artwork, fun story and side missions, two very likeable playable characters. New GTA-like carriage gameplay, if you're into that sort of thing.\nThe bad: Just about everything that's been wrong with AC since forever. Clunky combat, TONS of busywork and collect-a-thons, same models for just about every NPC you find, boring and obnoxious escort and follow missions.\nStill the most enjoyable AC game since Black Flag. Get it on sale.", "hours": 42.2, "user_id": "76561198077192492", "username": "Clauricaune", "products": 602, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 163, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-04", "text": "This game is hard to decide wether or not to recommend. I personally found the game EXTREMELY tedious. Everywhere you go seems to take forever and I usually don't complain about \"fluff\". Both Jacob and Evie were interesting enough to keep me playing all the way through, but Crawford Starric is support forgettable. I only remembered his name because I was talking about the game with my friends. I loved the gang stuff, and leveling up your \"companions\". I wish I could get to know their store better, but that's not a thing in this game.\nI would wait for a sale, I didn't and I kinda regret it. 7/10", "hours": 52.2, "username": "Thicc B01", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 163, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-03", "text": "If you like assassin's creed you will love this game.   It is like a much better version of unity with a xp system an gear crfting and you start a gang so it is awesome.  Also their are carriages so you have very carlike transport.  And you meet queen victoria charles darwin and dickens and alexander graham bell.  All in all I think it is the best assassin's creed game money can buy.  The charles dickens side missione are very interesting and go into the \"spirit world\" of things as was believed at that time.", "hours": 57.6, "user_id": "76561198190486269", "username": "SimonWagon", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
