{"product_id": "368500", "page": 167, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed Syndicate is what the franchise is all about. Keep in mind I didn't play Unity.\n- Visuals are beautiful\n- I love the battle system: you can view an enemy's level using eagle vision (V), the higher his/her level is the harder it is to counter their attacks. Gunshot have a window of opurtunity in which you can evade them buy pressing (F).\n- You can finally crouch (C) (again I didn't play Unity so for me this is new)\n- Parkour/Free running system improved in a way that suits industrial London. Instead of simply holding shift+W and climbing upwards or free running, you can hold shift+W + E to free run down or shift+W + Space to free run up. If your only holding shift + W you have no risk of jumping of high places.\nIf you loved Brotherhood you will definiately love Syndicate.", "hours": 58.1, "username": "1 \u2615 3989", "products": 486, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 167, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-19", "text": "Despite being worried I wasted my money on another Assassins Creed game after I said Rogue was where the series ended for me I'm so glad I was wrong. Probably one of the better titles in the series. There's so muc thats good about this game and with the news that Ubi isn't doing annual AC games anymore I'm hoping the series can recover some of its respect.\nPros\nGood Port (Even for AMD)\nGrapple Hook is an amazing tool\nStory\nCharacters\nThe City of London is never dull.\nCons\nRandom Crashes\nObnoxious British Accents\nNot alot of Fast Travel Locations (Sometimes driving carriages or running or jumping across the rooftops can get rather annoying)\nWould I recommend this? Absolutely. This is a good apology from Ubisoft after the nightmare that was Unity. *shivers*", "hours": 39.6, "username": "Heebrial Niijima", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 167, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-19", "text": "After the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665how that was Unity, I was very wary of Syndicate. Picked it up on sale and was thoroughly surprised by how much I enjoyed it.\nIt reminded me hugely of the Ezio trilogy, arguably the best Assassin's Creed games. The world feels perfect to travel across, the player characters are likable with each of them having their own goal for the creed.\nThe level up system is far better than the terrible idea in Unity where you must play through the missions and reach certain sequences before you could even get basic Assassin abilities. You can level up in any way in this game, unlock loads of brilliant abilities. Likewise with upgrading your gang (\"The Rooks\") and your gear.\n98% in the main game (enough for me, not bothered about 100%) and 100% in the Jack the Ripper DLC which was absolutely bloody fantastic, albeit very dark (no complaints, worked incredibly well).\nLike the older AC games, especially the Ezio trilogy? Burnt by the recent ones? Give this one a go, definitely great fun and a return to what AC should be.", "hours": 51.6, "username": "Havok16", "products": 839, "early_access": false}
