{"product_id": "368500", "page": 217, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-05", "text": "The game itself is fun, and a definite improvement over Unity in many ways - with the exception of some facial animations and lighting. The game itself runs fine: I get around 40 - 60 FPS in the open world (with no stuttering) on the high preset on an R9 280X, which is decent (could be better mind you, but I've played worse). There are some drawbacks, however: graphics settings are pretty limited (e.g. no anisotropic filtering, anti-aliasing is limited to nasty FXAA and MSAA combinations, can't turn off any of the post-process stuff), special/Gameworks graphics settings are nearly broken on Radeon (and apparently some Nvidia) cards and some cloth physics are limited to 30 FPS, which sounds anal as hell but you'll know exactly what I mean when you play it. But, overall, this is a solid port.", "hours": 49.7, "username": "Biggs98", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
