{"product_id": "368500", "page": 217, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-05", "text": "Let me start out by saying that I loved Unity. This game is basically a reskin of Unity, but it doesn't have all of the performance issues many people were having. It runs really solid even with high settings.\nThe story in this game is not as solid as some of the previous games, but the game makes up for it with the characters. I haven't had this much fun with AC characters since Ezio. Jacob and Evie are the best thing to happen to the series in my opinion.\nThere is lots of variety with missions and lots of ways to accomplish things. Combat has been made easier since Unity which opens up the possibility of going in guns blazing or picking one of the other methods. Speaking of which, I really love during assassination missions that there are multiple different ways presented to the player to accomplish it. That was something from Unity that I was glad Ubisoft kept, it's a great mechanic.\nThe ending was a let-down, but I don't think it could have outdone the ending in Unity.\nAll in all, I wish I could unplay this game just to play it again for the first time. I laughed a lot during it and really took an interest in the characters. The gameplay was fun and smooth. Besides, who doesn't love hijacking carriages from someone and leading police on a low-speed chase?", "hours": 19.8, "user_id": "76561198020471227", "username": "WolfEyes (Loki'd)", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 218, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-05", "text": "This is just a warning for people who have their games on a different drive from their system (C) drive. So if you're running an SSD for Windows and apps, while installing your games to a mechanical drive, you might not be able to run it without moving the audio files to your system drive (which seems to be the only fix) or installing the whole game on your system drive. To me this seems a bit sloppy not to test something like that in this day and age.\n*Childish idiots, please feel free to downvote and find 'funny'.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198128075408", "username": "SOYZUKI", "products": 138, "found_funny": 9, "early_access": false}
