{"product_id": "368500", "page": 218, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-04", "text": "Hands down one of the worst Assassins Creed titles released.\n- The game has more bugs than Unity.\n- AI is AWFUL.\n- The realism and difficulty have been brought down to appeal to 12 year-olds\n- Shameless \"in-app purchase\" options for XP and money.\n+ Collecting crap around the world actually unlocks useful upgrades instead of purely being achievement-based\nUbisoft has moved ever so far from the days of Altair, Ezio, and Connor. They're just milking the franchise, now.", "hours": 41.2, "username": "buzzy", "products": 83, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 218, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-04", "text": "Wow. Just, wow. I had little hope going into this game after Unity. But in the first hour of the game, I was blown away.\nStory: Likeable, funny characters and a nicely writen plot that keeps me on edge. 8/10\nOpen World: So diverse and big. Carriages, trains, and ziplines make it much easier to traverse the massive world. 7/10\nFighting mechanics: My least favorite part about the game. Simple and repetivie. Very dissapointing. 4/10\nStealth: So much more fun than Unity's \"stealth\" and makes you feel like a true Assassin.\nSkills and Customization: Skills are very helpful and beneficial. Customization isn't as diverse as Unity, but is still good. 6/10\nOverall, I can't tell you how much I reccomend this game to you. This has to be one of my favorite AC games ever. If you have the money and are a fan of the series, this is a definite buy.\n8/10 overall rating", "hours": 59.8, "user_id": "76561198089827088", "username": "Porg", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
