{"product_id": "368500", "page": 225, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "So far I'm loving this game!  Being immersed in London is awesome.  It takes a bit to get used to the controls, as I haven't really played other Assassin's Creed games much.  You do get the hang of it eventually though.  This one, is well worth it.  Quite an adventure so far!  Be warned - graphics requirements are quite high on this one - it's taxing my GTX 660ti, but I managed to get it looking good by using SweetFX 2.0 and lowering the in-game settings which helped my FPS.", "hours": 42.2, "username": "KoreReactor", "products": 77, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 225, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "suffers from not being Metal Gear Solid: The Phantom Pain, I.E. very clunky tanklike and sticky controls that the series is known for which is all well and dandy, but now that i KNOW how crisp and precise the controls for a stealth game CAN be it's borderline unplayable to me\noh and microtransactions lol, sure let me just pay irl money for a xp boost in your singleplayer game, guess you couldnt balance the xp gain then and the only option left was to demand more money instead\ninconsistent FPS and lack of optimisation + a nasty memory leak = refund and reinstall black flag, BACK TO THE HIGH SEAS BOYS\npoor cash-strapped ubisoft just cant afford to make a good PC port", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561197970756092", "username": "Butt Inspector", "products": 372, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 225, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "It is a good looking game, however it has several game braking glitches. 25 hours in and im glitched on a loading screen yet somehow still die in combat. I have deleted it and re-downloaded it and now i cant even attack. it was a good game at first but now i cant even play it. This game is a waste of $60.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "zumiez0898", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 225, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "Stunning graphics, great combat and item system similar to the batman franchise. The story moves a little slow but is quite decent and there is a lot to do and see. Great character customization and I like having two characters. I love Assassin's Creed, but the last few have been sub par,  but not this one. Also don't forget to pick up the two free customs!", "hours": 42.5, "user_id": "76561198097672475", "username": "Lostnfound", "products": 57, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 225, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-27", "text": "ACS is a huge improvment over the previous Assassin Creed games. It fixes many of the bugs of the last ones and London, which has been recreated, looks amazing and is a joy to explore. The gameplay is fun and exciting the new grappling hook makes getting around London so much fun. The new characters are great Jacob and Evie are my faviortite assassins since Ezio and there voice acting brings them to life so well. And with the large amount of content you get your moneys worth (espically if you are a completionist like me). Despite all the great things this game brings to the table it has its issues, one of the main things being that it changes NOTHING in the AC formula. This game is almost exactly the same as all the previous AC games and that is really disappointing the age old issues still appear here as well; the wall climbing is not fixed meaning there are times when jacob/Evie make a movment wrong and get caught or killed and this is extremly anoying, also the world content is very much the same thing over and over (I have also heard they ruin the end but I am not there yet). Overall this game is great despite all its flaws and is well worth getting!", "hours": 71.4, "user_id": "76561198085899780", "username": "Evo", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
