{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-24", "text": "Look, I'm gonna be honest here: this game isn't that great.\nIt's good.  Hell yeah, it's good.  But I mean, it's like a solid 75/100.\nWhat's good?  Well, the setting is done pretty well.  The main villain is interesting, and there's no more of that annoying modern day gameplay (at least so far in my playthrough).  I'm enjoying the story, such as it is.\nNow for the bad: the freerunning is messy as hell.  I was trying to climb down from a crate, using only the button that is -expressly for descending -, and I just kind of kept hopping off and then on to one ledge.  I mean, it's pretty bad.  Your \"stronghold\" (since every AC game needs one of those, evidently) is a train this time around, which is a cool idea in theory, but in practice it just means that you have to figure out where on the map your stronghold is at any given time (did I mention it moves?), and figure out how to intercept it.  The train is probably the absolute worst thing about this game, and it was intentional.  I mean, not intentionally bad, but you know...it's working as designed, it's just that the design is awful.  A bunch of missions can only be done from the train, too, which makes that especially annoying.  NPC's glitch out all the time.  I had one glitch where I just had an enemy that kept respawning around this one corner.  I farmed about 70 of them before I got bored and found something else to do.  I also regularly see children diving off of ledges, sometimes several stories up.  While I mentioned that the bad guy is pretty cool and interesting, he's also not nearly utilized enough.  I'd have preferred something like the amount of characterization we got with Haytham back in AC3, which was one of the few story-related things that game got right.\nThe combat is....Assassin's creed.  You don't play this series for the combat.  If a good combat system is what you want, then I have no idea why you would even play this.\nI mean, I know it sounds like a lot more bad than good, but I'm enjoying it.  I'd recommend it.  I just would recommend it with a bigass asterisk next to that recommendation, because it's good but nothing amazing.", "hours": 85.6, "username": "TehBastage", "products": 366, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-24", "text": "Just finished the campaign. Wonderful experience. Had enough of nice cutscenes to tell a decent story. Nice to be able to swtich character most of the time. I loved Elise from ACU, and Evie Frye didn't disappoint either. Did I mention pretty as well? AC series has such strong female characters. Nice to have a happy ending (in contrast to ACU). The ending brought a tear to my eyes. Alas, all good things will come to an end ... a memorable end, though. Will remember Elise & Evie for a long time. :) Technically, this PC version is sound. Had a few occasions where the game either hangs or have some glitch. None too bothersome though. Restarted and everything's fine again. This game is much more optimized and bug-free then ACU. Nice to have automatic saving too (while RPGs often require you to do tedious manual saving every now & then). Well, the animation of the fighting action impressed me too. The character models are nice. The crowds are there on the streets, making London a lively city. Was not able to buy Helix & XP points with real money though. Just got an error message. Well, nothing that can't be solved with a bit of grinding. Overall, looking forward to next year's game. :)", "hours": 82.6, "user_id": "76561198008643395", "username": "R6ex", "products": 304, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-24", "text": "Only up to level 4 yet, but so far I'm loving it.  If you like Assassin's Creed style, It's more of the same.  I like that they have added back (?) crafting.  The main story line with the Twins has been fun and interesting so far.  They re-added a  Different side quests, and as always, the hunt for chests!  I foresee being lost in this game for many many hours to come.  They brought back a version of the Zip line, which makes getting around the city easier.  like the gritty feel of the industrial revolution London.", "hours": 69.9, "user_id": "76561198055420167", "username": "Friday", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-23", "text": "Simplemente lo am\u00e9!!!\nlas misiones, la personalidad de los gemelos, la historia, las peleas. Realmente no tengo nada malo que decir de \u00e9ste juego con excepci\u00f3n de que en la secuencia 7 en una de las memorias hay un bug que facilmente se puede evitar (si digo de que se trata doy spoilers) ya cuando lleguen se dar\u00e1n cuenta), esperemos con el parche lo corrijan, pero, como ya mencion\u00e9, se \"evita\" facilmente\nde ah\u00ed en m\u00e1s, el juego, al menos en m\u00ed computadora, anduvo perfecto, no tuve ning\u00fan problema con ninguna otra misi\u00f3n\ncomo ver\u00e1n por mis horas de juego, es m\u00e1s o menos lo que me tom\u00f3 el completar todas las misiones (con un 100 % sincronizaci\u00f3n), investigar Londres, completar colecciones\nLa verdad que para que sea m\u00e1s entretenido hacer las misiones tienen que hacer los retos opcionales para que no lo sientan repetitivo (a muchos les pasa)\nVali\u00f3 la pena el gasto y la espera, si eres fan de assassins creed esto te gustara. :D", "hours": 191.0, "username": "Aydin", "products": 198, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-23", "text": "It really pains me to do this,but i cannot in good sense recomend this game anymore.Or atleast not after what Ubisoft did! So ubi just released the last Piece of \"DLC\" for the game.The dreadful crimes missions. Though Ubisoft made no promises of giving this content free,it is a given because it was a part of the game at launch and exclusive to one console(PS4).Now not only is it paid,it is also not included in the season pass!So great job at \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing us up Ubisoft!\nUsually iam not one of those idiots who would jump on to the all hate Ubisoft bandwagon,but this is completely unacceptable!", "hours": 233.3, "username": "Wulfrix", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 229, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-23", "text": "This game is good but it's utter\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665when it comes to performance.\nI'm running 4 way GTX 980 SLI an intel  i7 5960X 32GB of Corsair Domintator Platinum DDR4 2666MHz and im getting 40 frames at Ultra Setting with just AA disabled at 1440p.WHAT THE \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 UBISOFT I'M GETTING A REFUND\nSLI IS \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ED IN MOST GAMES.If your going to buy 2 weaker gpus than buy 1 stronger gpu JUST DONT.Save up money for the next GTX Titan X and buy 1 beast GPU dont go SLI like i did it's a waste of money, it causes a lot lot more heat in your system, more noise and finally MORE MONEY.Most games out there dont benift from SLI or just stutter like hell or just arent worth spending more money on another GPU.\nI just really hope Just Cause 3 doesn't end up like Assassins Creed Syndicate because if it does i'm going to overclock the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665out of my 3 other GTX 980s turn off all the fans in my system run the GPU fan speed at the lowest and run the most hardware intensive application out there and just cook eggs on them.", "hours": 2.5, "user_id": "76561198159073139", "username": "StrigoiVampirism", "products": 48, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
