{"product_id": "368500", "page": 233, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-22", "text": "I am a big fan of this series. I have been playing since the begining. I feel that there have been a few games in the series that fell short and had me wanting more. My overall favorite was Assassins Creed 2.  So far Ive made it through the begining part of the game and unlocked a small portion of what is yet to come. And I can honestly say I am excited. This brings the feel of the original Assassins with a few new twists.  Also another nice thing about this game is the made it playable with a controller on PC, a big plus in my book. OH YEAH AND THOSE FRECKLES !!!! OMFnG", "hours": 46.3, "username": "AnonymousNck", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 233, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-22", "text": "This is only a first impressions review for now, but I must say I was very much pleasantly surprised with this game.\nPerformance-wise, especially. I have a GTX 950, so not that beefy of a GPU, but I was able to run this game smoothly with medium settings, and the game still looked great. Often with games the lower settings always ended up being significantly uglier, but this game is still quite the looker even in medium graphic settings. I had around 60-30 FPS while playing, and it never dropped below 30, even in the denser areas. Mostly stayed around 60 to 50, which was totally fine for me and gave me a smooth enough experience.\nWhat also gave me a pleasant surprise was the gameplay itself. With AC games I usually get bored within the first hour or so, but I can tell I'm going to be investing a lot of time into this game, because it's such a fresh new take on the AC franchise. I'm obsessed with the stealth system this time around, especially since I've always found the stealth aspect in the AC games to be lackluster, ironically. And the combat is so much more fluid and fun.\nEven the characters I already like. Evie and Jacob each have their own personalities, so they're not just wooden planks like whoever was the name of that main character from Unity.\nI was strongly against buying this game at first, but now I honestly don't regret doing so. I haven't been this thrilled over an AC game in a long, LONG time, and frankly I thought I never would be again. But so far, I'm loving what I'm seeing.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Shady Boots", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
