{"product_id": "368500", "page": 238, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-20", "text": "cant believe im saying this but its the first UBI game that actually is good optimized, aside from that PCSS frame rate killer option everything else works great and is an incredible stable game, usually with open world games you get the odds spots were the frame drops without explanation, this game is very stable all over the place in gameplay, cutscenes the frame tends to drop but not by much, about the game i have to say is awesome, after unity i didnt think i would get another AC game but after renting the ps4 version it convinced me that unity was just a fluke, so i decided to wait for this version and the wait was worth it, great job UBI, now please DO NOT SCREW UP THE DIVISION!", "hours": 19.5, "user_id": "76561198035808254", "username": "dEvAnGeL", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "368500", "page": 238, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-20", "text": "Until now I DONT recommend this game. It has way too many bugs and glitches. Currently Im stucked inside a house because of the R item..\n- Some times the npcs AI just stops working. The enemy stop attacking you and you can do whatever you want until the mission is complete.\n- Many times when I have my view to right right and want to move to the left it moves to the right.\n- I took one npc as hostage in a mission. While hostage my char kept moving by itself away from the horse. When I want to move to the horse it keep blocking like there was a wall.\n- The movement with E and SPACE suck so hard.\n- The story is complete\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and so boring.\n- Everything is way too easy. Im lv 2 and complete lv 5 missions.\nThis game compared to assassins creed 1 or 2 is COMPLETE garbage. Dont waste 70euro on it. This game is worth 10 euro but not more.", "hours": 7.5, "username": "Daneos", "products": 31, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
