{"product_id": "368500", "page": 250, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-19", "text": "After playing Fallout 4, and now Syndicates, there is such a shocking contrast that it has opened my eyes to how much Ubisoft is streets ahead of their competition!\nThis game runs brilliantly on my GTX970 -- the attention to detail in these games is truely incredible.\nIt makes Fallout 4 look like a bunch of amateurs! Their \"cities\" are a couple of houses plopped in a field, here is a detailed city that sprawls endlessly where every location is still unique and is \"alive\".\nI can't recommend this game enough!\nIt's fun, London is amazing, the characters voices and motion capture are awesome (Ubisoft really is amazing at this).\nAnd to anyone contemplating Fallout 4, go buy Dying Light which is a much much better game than Fallout 4.", "hours": 21.3, "user_id": "76561197998961393", "username": "joelvanvelden", "products": 109, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
